reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Runs Amazing but too hot.
reviews.reviewText: Amazing for the price and runs basically any game you throw at it at Med to High at 1440p. The only complaint that I have is that it runs super super hot. At max load it will reach 89C which doesn’t make me comfortable. I’m not sure if this is the manufacturer or AMD software at fault. Make sure you unlock fans’ locked speed in AMD Driver Software. It will subsequently drop to around 73C under max load.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars WARNING!!!! COIL WHINE AND DRIVER ISSUES!!!!
reviews.reviewText: I was building my first pc ever and almost everything went well. I had everything finished and it was time to turn it on and everything worked. After setting up everything like windows, games, etc, I played some games like apex legends, fortnite, rocket league and more. PART1: Now this is the part you have to pay attention. When I played games that didn’t require much gpu or cpu utilization everything was pretty quite. HOWEVER when I played games that required about 60+ utilization of the gpu like apex and fortnite I started hearing a buzzing noise coming from the gpu. THIS IS CALLED COIL WHINE. Although this doesn’t hurt the performance of the gpu, it can be annoying to listen to if you don’t have headphones in or something.Part 2: GPU DRIVER ISSUES. While setting up my pc I was downloading motherboard drivers and gpu drivers. When I was downloading gpu drivers I got a message saying that I needed to reboot/restart my pc. I went to restart my pc and my monitor turned off but my pc stayed on AND FOR SOME REASON MY FANS WERE BLOWING AT FULL SPEED. I WAS PANICKING BECAUSE THIS WAS MY FIRST PC BUILD WHICH I HAD USED SOME GOOD MONEY FOR. I had to turn off my pc by the power button because nothing was happening except my fans blowing at full rpm. IF ANYONE SEEING THIS HAS THE SAME PROBLEM THEN FOLLOW THESE STEPS: Step 1. Turn off psu by the switch. Step 2. Unplug monitor and psu cable from power strip. Step 3. Plug monitor and psu cable back in then switch the psu back on. Step 4. Press power button on pc and it should boot up now on the monitor. SIDE NOTE THIS DOES NOT FIX THE DRIVER ISSUE IF YOU RESTART THEN THE ISSUE WILL HAPPEN AGAIN. HOWEVER AFTER RESTARTING MY PC AND UNPLUGGING EVERYTHING OUT AND BACK IN A COUPLE OF TIMES I MANAGED TO GET RID OF THE DRIVER ISSUE (KEEP IN MIND IM WRITING THIS REVIEW THE SAME DAY I HAD DRIVER ISSUES SO THIS ISSUE CAN HAPPEN AGAIN IN THE FUTURE).Part 3: Kind of bad temps. I looked up videos of people with a similar build with mine and I looked at their gpu temps while they were gaming and mine would always be higher in every game by about 5-10°C (same settings as theirs).Part 4: MY EXPECTATIONS FOR THIS GPU WERE NOT MET. I THOUGHT I WOULD GET WAY HIGHER FPS THAN I ACTUALLY DO. THIS GPU CAN BARELY GET 140 FPS AT 1080p MEDIUM/HIGH SETTINGS ON MOST GAMES. I PLAY ON A 144 FPS MONITOR AND I THOUGHT THIS GPU WOULD BE ABLE TO KEEP IT AT 144 FPS AT ALL TIMES BUT IT CANT. THERE IS ALSO ALOT OF 1% LOW FPS CHANGES AND THIS IS BAD BECAUSE WHEN YOURE PLAYING, YOUR SCREEN LAGS WHILE CHANGING THOSE FRAMES.OVERALL I WOULD RECOMMEND GETTING THIS GPU FROM ANOTHER BRAND LIKE SAPPHIRE OR MSI. I MIGHT HAVE BEEN JUST UNLUCKY AND GOT A GPU WITH COIL WHINE AND BAD THERMAL PASTE APPLICATION BUT PLEASE BE AWARE OF THESE ISSUES THAT YOU COULD HAVE IF YOU PURCHASE FROM THIS BRAND. PLEASE DO RESEARCH BEFORE BUYING THIS GPU.

reviews.reviewTitle: its good but its not the one
reviews.reviewText: if you are on the market for a 6650xt get this on sale but regularly there are cheaper variants out there

Comprata come upgrade di un pc da gaming dotato di ryzen 7 2700x, la scheda è eccezionale: regge qualsiasi gioco in 1080p a qualsiasi impostazione, e con il software adrenalin di amd supporta anche parecchie opzioni di miglioramento grafico e upscaling, ovviamente non fa miracoli, dipende molto anche dalla cpu che le si affianca, tuttavia un grande upgrade (vengo da una rx570).La scheda è molto robusta, con un backplate di alluminio pressofuso nella parte superiore che la rende discreta ed elegante, non ho riscontrato rumori molesti da parte delle ventole, ricordiamo che xfx, sapphire e asrock sono le scelte migliori per quanto riguarda customizzazioni amd, poichè sono partner ufficiali, quindi anche il supporto hardware è dedicato appositamente ai chip venduti, scelta ottima anche per il prezzo, consigliata
